Source : https://dzone.com/articles/how-to-run-docker-container-on-your-local-machine

step 1: Build Docker Image
docker build -t {{image-name}} .

docker build -t ndusystems2019/fundani.api .

step 2: run docker image
docker run -p 8600:80 -it {{image-name}}

docker run -p 8600:80 -it fundani.api
to stop image = ctr + c


Step 3: After testing that everything works as expected Push.
docker push ndusystems2019/fundani.api 

